{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_0179LFcS1miPA4429mzQgnuq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The answer is directly visible in the pre-fetched context — no exploration or planning needed.\n\n**File:** `server/services/executor-registry.ts`\n**Class:** `ExecutorRegistry` (lines 52-84)\n**Registration method:** `register(nodeType: string, executor: NodeExecutor): void`\n\nThe registry maps node types to executors using an internal `Map<string, NodeExecutor>` called `executors`. The `register` method stores an executor under its `nodeType` key (`this.executors.set(nodeType, executor)`), and `get(nodeType)` retrieves it later.\n\nIt also has two sibling registration methods for special cases:\n- `registerConditional(nodeType, executor)` — for branching nodes (IF/Switch) that route items to multiple outputs\n- `registerPassThrough(nodeType)` — for sub-node types that carry config but don't execute\n\nNote: the class exists, but `server/services/workflow-executor.ts` doesn't actually use it — `WorkflowExecutor` still dispatches via a long `if (currentNode.type === \"...\")` chain. So the registry appears to be infrastructure not yet wired into the main executor.\n\nSince this is a read-only Q&A and no plan is needed, I'll exit plan mode without writing a plan file."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":36760,"cache_read_input_tokens":19320,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":36760},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce3a8e26-fb94-40b9-bf38-dee9186611a9","uuid":"1a96e13f-6701-4104-85f0-ad08b732ffcf"}
